\mathcal{X}
\mathcal{F}=\{f_i : \mathcal{X} \to \mathbb{R}\}_{i=1}^k
\mathcal{X}
\mathcal{F}
\alpha_{\mathcal{X},\mathcal{F}}\in\mathbb{R}
X\in \mathcal{X}
\hat{X}\in\mathcal{X}
i\in[k]
 f_i(\hat{X}) \leq \alpha_{\mathcal{X},\mathcal{F}} \mathbb{E}\{ f_i(X)\}
\mathcal F = \{ f_i : \mathbb R\rightarrow \mathbb R,\;  f_i \text{ convex},  \; f_i \in L^1 \}_{i=1}^k 
 f_i(\hat X) \leq \mathbb E[f_i(X)] \quad  \alpha_{\mathbb R, \mathcal F} = 1 
